---
description: Rust + Axum coding and API conventions
globs: backend/**/*.rs
alwaysApply: false
---
# Rust
- Format with `rustfmt`, pass `clippy`.
- Use `thiserror` for error types; map to HTTP responses in one place.
- No `unwrap()` / `expect()`; propagate typed errors with `?`.
- Keep modules small: handlers, services, domain logic in separate files.

# Axum API
- Handlers return `Result<_, AppError>`; never panic.
- JSON payloads as `serde` DTOs; do not expose internal domain types.
- Validate inputs (lengths, required fields, query/pagination limits).
- Use `axum::extract::State` for shared deps (index writer/searcher).
- Every endpoint needs automated tests (integration + service-level unit tests).

# Observability
- `tracing` with structured fields only (no `println!`); include request-scoped id.

# Security
- Authn/authz on the backend (middleware or service layer).
- Enforce payload size limits and timeouts; configure CORS to allowed origins only.
- Never log secrets/credentials; error responses must not leak internals.
